HEADWORD: Suine
<hw>Su"ine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Suint</er>.]</ety> <def>A mixture of oleomargarine with lard or
other fatty ingredients. It is used as a substitute for butter. See
<er>Butterine</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

